    "caption": "No brain, no bones, no blood — and still one of the most successful animals in the sea.",
    "shortDescription": "Jellyfish have drifted through the world's oceans for over five hundred million years, outlasting dinosaurs, ice ages, and every mass extinction so far. Their body is ninety-five percent water, they have no brain or heart, and yet they sting, hunt, and reproduce with quiet efficiency. Fun fact: One species of jellyfish, the immortal jellyfish, can revert to its juvenile form when stressed — essentially hitting a biological reset button."
